<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">greywolffe</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Question:  Has anyone noticed a change in their ability to make a train?  Not saying by accident but on purpose with the intention of using an AoE to derail it.<P>I have been sitting on the Grimrot camp for several days now and would attempt to agro all the skellies I could then Upheaval (over-kill I know) them in one shot.  Well it seems I can only keep 3 or 4 aggro'd on me while running around.  Once I come into aggro range of the 5th one, one of the original mobs will pop back to it's spawn spot.<P>I've tested this out in Runnyeye (King's room) with the same effect.  I cannot keep more than 3 or 4 mobs "trained" at any given time.  Am I doing something wrong?  Was there a change?<P>Thanks,<BR>Greywollfe<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kajoraa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">try to sit down right in the middle of the camp<P>that was my strategy  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Kajoraa Xinach`Xa<BR>50th DE cleric of Innoruuk (BB)<BR>&lt;The Imperium Knights&gt;</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Xthor</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yes, I was trying that exact same thing at the Grimrot spawn the other day and noticed the same thing.  When I ended up doing was training some of the outlying ones to the center and trying to hit a couple before they aggrod with the train I was pulling.<P>Xthor Mednheal<BR>Cleric of 38 Seasons<BR>Solace Keep<BR>Druzzil Ro</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gello</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah I've noticed it in MM when fixing VP/RoS faction.  A reliable work around is to load up Stun Command.  (or regular stun to get one extra mob)  If only 4 will attack, and there are 7 total you aggro'd, stun commanding the closest 3 around you will cause the 3 others to resume running at you.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">brom</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nothing has changed did grimrot camps months ago same thing cant train more than 3 or 4 at a time there.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Huffadopolis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I can't remember where I read it, but I recall that you can't have more than 3 mobs actively aggroed on you at once.<P>I have tested this (outdoors only, not indoors yet) and it's true.  Go to qeynos hills, or sro, or somewhere where you can aggro 10+ things safely on yourself..then run ahead of them and wait to see what happens.  You'll notice that once three are engaged with you, the rest start wandering off.  THen when you kill one of the three, one of the ones that wandered off will run up to you and start whacking on you.  This continues until all aggroed on you are dead.<P>Like I said, I haven't tested this indoors, but outdoors, 3 is the magic number.<P>------------------<BR>Huffadopolis Polychronopolis<BR>Level 52 Halfling Vicar<BR>Arma Aquetatis<BR>Lanys T`Vyl</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cenge</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My rogue ( a lowly level 4 mind you) managed to train about 15 armadillows (i know i killed that spelling).<P>Thats a little but more than 3 or 4.<P>------------------<BR>Do I look like a "happy" healer to you? ~ Cenge</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Darianne</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR>There was a change made awhile back... you can only engage 3 mobs at a time.<P>If you dont believe me, go pick some fights... have them follow you... only 3 will attack, a 4th will stand back and watch... if you kill one, that extra will come in and attack.<P>As soon as the agro spreads to more than one person, I think there is not cap (for example, I think two people fighting, can be atacked by 20 mobs).</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I noticed it too but i thought it was just the zone I was in cause it was new. I was in the Warrens trying to get my faction up for the Paineel quests. I would run in and fear and AoE and get like 20 puppies on me then run around and try and get more, then by the time i turned around my train was 3:P </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
